    "time_total_min": 20,
    "steps": [
      {
        "step_no": 1,
        "text": "Make the tapenade: combine pitted olives, green olives, capers, garlic, anchovy (if using), lemon juice, parsley and olive oil in a food processor or bowl. Pulse or mash until a coarse, spreadable paste forms; scrape down sides and taste, adjusting lemon, oil or salt as needed.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Toast the bread: heat a skillet over medium and add butter or olive oil. Add bread slices and cook until golden and crisp on both sides, about 1–2 minutes per side, or toast in a toaster until well-browned. Keep warm.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Fry the eggs: in the same skillet over medium-low, add a small pat of butter or a drizzle of oil. Crack eggs into skillet and cook until whites are set but yolks remain runny for sunny-side-up, about 3–4 minutes; cover for even cooking. For over-easy, flip gently and cook 20–30 seconds more.",
        "time_min": 6
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Assemble: spread a generous layer of tapenade on each toasted slice. Place a fried egg on top, season with black pepper and optional crushed red pepper. Garnish with parsley or microgreens and serve immediately.",
